[
    {
        "text": "The Land of Salt and Fire",
        "start": 8.46,
        "duration": 3.514
    },
    {
        "text": "Dallol, Ethiopia",
        "start": 14.064,
        "duration": 2.55
    },
    {
        "text": "It is so hot here,",
        "start": 18.004,
        "duration": 1.915
    },
    {
        "text": "the hottest place on earth.",
        "start": 19.919,
        "duration": 2.61
    },
    {
        "text": "I come here to push my imagination.",
        "start": 24.523,
        "duration": 2.47
    },
    {
        "text": "To see something new.",
        "start": 26.993,
        "duration": 2.01
    },
    {
        "text": "To understand how this place",
        "start": 31.19,
        "duration": 1.89
    },
    {
        "text": "is possible, I’ll take you to the white.",
        "start": 33.08,
        "duration": 2.47
    },
    {
        "text": "To the salt.",
        "start": 36.66,
        "duration": 2.017
    },
    {
        "text": "I’m Andrea Frazzetta, there on the back",
        "start": 50.459,
        "duration": 1.869
    },
    {
        "text": "of the car, with the camera.",
        "start": 52.328,
        "duration": 1.695
    },
    {
        "text": "I’m a photographer.",
        "start": 54.023,
        "duration": 1.569
    },
    {
        "text": "And we are driving across the bottom",
        "start": 59.25,
        "duration": 1.819
    },
    {
        "text": "of an ancient ocean,",
        "start": 61.069,
        "duration": 1.628
    },
    {
        "text": "now a thick bed of salt.",
        "start": 62.697,
        "duration": 2.183
    },
    {
        "text": "It is so hot you can imagine how",
        "start": 72.807,
        "duration": 1.989
    },
    {
        "text": "10,000 years ago the sun evaporated",
        "start": 74.796,
        "duration": 2.139
    },
    {
        "text": "the ocean, leaving behind the",
        "start": 76.935,
        "duration": 1.796
    },
    {
        "text": "vast plain of salt.",
        "start": 78.731,
        "duration": 2.287
    },
    {
        "text": "Salt that the Afar people",
        "start": 87.499,
        "duration": 1.986
    },
    {
        "text": "have been mining for centuries.",
        "start": 89.485,
        "duration": 2.066
    },
    {
        "text": "They shape the salt into those blocks",
        "start": 96.216,
        "duration": 2.03
    },
    {
        "text": "at your feet to sell at market.",
        "start": 98.246,
        "duration": 2.419
    },
    {
        "text": "The blocks were once so valuable",
        "start": 108.371,
        "duration": 1.812
    },
    {
        "text": "they were used as money.",
        "start": 110.183,
        "duration": 2.013
    },
    {
        "text": "The miners are working now, but the week",
        "start": 114.757,
        "duration": 1.983
    },
    {
        "text": "before, they had gone on strike",
        "start": 116.74,
        "duration": 1.987
    },
    {
        "text": "to protest the falling price of salt.",
        "start": 118.727,
        "duration": 2.91
    },
    {
        "text": "I met a man named Kedir",
        "start": 130.424,
        "duration": 1.688
    },
    {
        "text": "who cut salt for 46 years.",
        "start": 132.112,
        "duration": 2.699
    },
    {
        "text": "\"The salt is right here on our doorstep.",
        "start": 136.17,
        "duration": 2.654
    },
    {
        "text": "Our fathers mined salt to raise us",
        "start": 138.824,
        "duration": 3.837
    },
    {
        "text": "and we do it to raise our children.",
        "start": 142.661,
        "duration": 3.535
    },
    {
        "text": "In the hot season, we hire help.”",
        "start": 146.196,
        "duration": 2.204
    },
    {
        "text": "“I think, in the future, the government",
        "start": 156.066,
        "duration": 3.46
    },
    {
        "text": "will give the work to outside companies,",
        "start": 159.526,
        "duration": 2.855
    },
    {
        "text": "and that the traditional way we mine salt",
        "start": 165.281,
        "duration": 2.909
    },
    {
        "text": "with camel caravans will end.”",
        "start": 168.19,
        "duration": 3.728
    },
    {
        "text": "Roads are being built in this area",
        "start": 177.981,
        "duration": 2.164
    },
    {
        "text": "of Ethiopia, which brings access,",
        "start": 180.145,
        "duration": 2.1
    },
    {
        "text": "and new mining techniques. If it’s easier",
        "start": 182.245,
        "duration": 3.076
    },
    {
        "text": "to move the salt, that means fewer",
        "start": 185.321,
        "duration": 2.876
    },
    {
        "text": "camel caravans each week.",
        "start": 188.197,
        "duration": 2.22
    },
    {
        "text": "Across the salt plain, there is another",
        "start": 198.684,
        "duration": 2.231
    },
    {
        "text": "industry growing. Tourism.",
        "start": 200.915,
        "duration": 3.135
    },
    {
        "text": "That’s Ali. His father was a salt miner.",
        "start": 221.489,
        "duration": 2.653
    },
    {
        "text": "But Ali has chosen a different path.",
        "start": 224.142,
        "duration": 3.104
    },
    {
        "text": "\"I work as a local guide to bring tourists",
        "start": 231.878,
        "duration": 3.332
    },
    {
        "text": "to Dallol.\"",
        "start": 235.21,
        "duration": 2.233
    },
    {
        "text": "\"I have lived in Dallol all my life.",
        "start": 242.362,
        "duration": 2.254
    },
    {
        "text": "Every day brings new things.",
        "start": 244.616,
        "duration": 3.79
    },
    {
        "text": "New people, new colors.",
        "start": 248.406,
        "duration": 3.287
    },
    {
        "text": "It never stops changing.\"",
        "start": 251.693,
        "duration": 4.002
    },
    {
        "text": "Because just under our feet is one of the",
        "start": 262.381,
        "duration": 2.763
    },
    {
        "text": "most active tectonic zones in the world.",
        "start": 265.144,
        "duration": 2.644
    },
    {
        "text": "Magma heats the groundwater, pushing it up",
        "start": 271.859,
        "duration": 1.985
    },
    {
        "text": "through cracks in the crust of the earth.",
        "start": 273.844,
        "duration": 2.486
    },
    {
        "text": "The water mixes with minerals and the salt",
        "start": 279.503,
        "duration": 2.684
    },
    {
        "text": "to create these rock formations and colors.",
        "start": 282.187,
        "duration": 3.122
    },
    {
        "text": "Sulphur makes the yellow,",
        "start": 288.632,
        "duration": 1.995
    },
    {
        "text": "copper makes the green.",
        "start": 290.627,
        "duration": 2.357
    },
    {
        "text": "Iron brings the red.",
        "start": 293.654,
        "duration": 2.412
    },
    {
        "text": "This landscape, a geyser island sitting",
        "start": 308.727,
        "duration": 2.851
    },
    {
        "text": "in the middle of the vast salt plain,",
        "start": 311.578,
        "duration": 2.675
    },
    {
        "text": "is like no other place in the world.",
        "start": 314.253,
        "duration": 2.469
    },
    {
        "text": "It’s a reminder that, just as the Afar",
        "start": 333.968,
        "duration": 2.301
    },
    {
        "text": "adapt to the forces that are changing",
        "start": 336.269,
        "duration": 2.009
    },
    {
        "text": "their traditional way of life, the earth",
        "start": 338.278,
        "duration": 3.234
    },
    {
        "text": "keeps shaping and shifting under our feet.",
        "start": 341.512,
        "duration": 5.62
    }
]